Nice fruity smell. Thick, long lasting head, .
Soft citrus taste, subtle earl grey, Creamy body. A really nice long lasting bitter finish

I love it.
Roasty, coffee like aroma, sparkling, black appearance.
 brown foam, medium sweetness, A subtle bitterness, medium kind of creamy body, lively Carbonation, long after taste.
Probably my new favourite Trappistastringent,
Nothing special, just another pilsener. But price/quality rating is pretty good.(almost half the price of an A-brand pilsener)

Nice dark red/brown color. Off-white head. A full and nice sour, woody, vinegar  like smell.
Going by the smell, i expected it to have a more sour taste..
light body, soft carbonation, long finish, 
Nice enjoyable beer. But i like the normal Rodenbach more.

33cl can from Dirk III
Smell is decent .
 Pale color. Sweet, hoppy taste, Metal-like after taste.Not a strong body. Way to Watery. Kinda reminds me of Jupiler Force (especialy the "Zesty kind"). Only worse.
Its not bad, but meh...
